Ishmael Wadada Leo Smith (born December 18, 1941) is an American trumpeter and composer, working primarily in the fields of avant-garde jazz and free improvisation.
He was one of three finalists for the 2013 Pulitzer Prize for Music for Ten Freedom Summers, released on May 22, 2012.

In 1971, Smith formed his own label, Kabell.
He also formed another band, the New Dalta Ahkri, with members including Henry Threadgill, Anthony Davis and Oliver Lake.In the 1970s, Smith studied ethnomusicology at Wesleyan University.
In 1993, he began teaching at Cal Arts, a position he held until 2014.
